  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9c\u0baa\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b9a \u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b86\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0baa\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka faces political risks due to new government's links to Rajapaksa family - Pitch",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka faces a political risk for the new government due to its links to the Rajapaksa family, according to Pitch Ratings.",
        "The pitch rating agency said that Sri Lanka is facing political crises related to the currency crisis and the recovery from the banking crisis.",
        "The majority for the new president has been confirmed in parliament and the government has also absorbed some opposition members, Pitch said.",
        "This gives the government confidence that it will find enough support to negotiate and push through tough reforms to restore economic stability and creditworthiness, Pitch said.",
        "Such reforms could lead to the availability of IMF financial support, which we believe is necessary for Sri Lanka to recover from its debt crisis, Pitch said.",
        "Members of the Rajapaksa family were ousted by protesters but the administration lacked popular support due to its ties to the Rajapaksa government.",
        "Parliamentary support for the government is strong but popular support is very weak, the PITCH rating agency noted.",
        "The current president, who served as prime minister in the government of the former president who was ousted by protesters, and whose parliament and cabinet are dominated by Sri Lanka Budujana Peramuna politicians, a party with close ties to the Rajapaksa family, Pitch said, adding that the government's ties to the Rajapaksa family could lead to destabilizing protests if economic conditions do not improve or public opposition to reforms develops. Pitch said.",
        "Pitch mentioned that we expect that the reforms that Sri Lanka may come to comply with the International Monetary Fund may include higher taxes, cost control and a commitment to flexibility in the exchange rate."
      ],
